  <exercise id="fs-id1104906" type="ap-test-prep">
  <problem id="fs-id3938320">
  <para id="fs-id2669847">In Millikan’s oil drop experiment, he experimented with various voltage differences between two plates to determine what voltage was necessary to hold a drop motionless. He deduced that the charge on the oil drop could be found by setting the gravitational force on the drop (pointing downward) equal to the electric force (pointing upward):</para>
